Add arguments.

Add easy color args.
-r red
-g green
-b blue
-y yellow
-k black
-m magenta
-c cyan
-w white

--help     
--version
--dash      Change the - character that gets output.
-n --columnsForce the number of columns to output.
-8          Force 80 columns to output.
--nounicode Supress default unicode
--title     Calculate center of string so I can add a section title.
--bs        Before space (default 0)
--as        After space  (default 0)
--surrond   Surronds the title in between two dl lines.

Instead of title being argument, put after command:
dl "Hello World"
outputs: ------ Hello World -------


On small screens with longer title, surrond the text:
------------
Hello World 
------------
(COLUMNS=12)



Add -L
Add -R
To left indent and right indent the title
-n 40 -L:
Hello ----------------------------------
-n 40 -R:
---------------------------------- World

